				<td colspan="2"><span>I have to say this method is unbalanced risk/reward. At least at lower levels, it is really out of line with every other exp-gaining method in the game that I have yet experienced (I've done it all too, except pre-POP high end AE groups I only did a couple times, they might have been comparable).  
<br />

<br />
Not only that, but if you do it in populated areas, it does border on rule-breaking ('monopolizing' a area, and zone disruption).
<br />

<br />
I don't consider it an exploit, but I would be totallly unsurprised if it got nerfed. 
<br />

<br />
I am a really poor ae kiter (poor WASD skills, never pull more than 15 mobs at a time, out of range a lot, die a lot) and I got from lvl 23 to 39 in a week of pretty casual play on my newbie bard on FV. That week included my learning curve where I died every other pull or so.  Without any outside buffs at all, with crappy gear, and without resses when I died, which was pretty frequent.  That's just a quantum difference between that, and any other exp method in the game. 
<br />

<br />
I guess my point is stop boasting and do it in out of the way areas where you don't interfere with others :p</span></td>
