				<td colspan="2"><span>See...It isn't entirely easy to kite this way.  That is one reason it probably wouldn't be nerfed.  It isn't as easy as some of the ways a warrior can solo really good places(yes it is possible and legit) or a shaman can solo dragons...Or a chanter can hold good portions of Sebilis with dire charm etc...etc...etc...
<br />

<br />
As for monopolizing an area...
<br />
Does a group not do this?
<br />
If a group was holding the same space would you have a problem with it?
<br />

<br />
If I AE kite a camp and people don't like it they can kiss my fast moving butt.  I didn't complain when some group wandered into Unrest and cut my mob count in half.  I just camped the space a group would camp.
<br />

<br />
If one player is disrupting a zone that player is the problem not the technique.
<br />

<br />
As for interfering with others?  So what?  I have as much right to that mob or camp as anyone or any group.  If I can hold it then guess what I'm going to do?  If I'm not dragging mobs over people or training the zone too much it is no one's business what I camp.
<br />

<br />
I will say one thing against what I said just then...
<br />
If I pulled the entire zone and kited it that would be different.  However pulling 20+ mobs that weren't going to get killed anyway doesn't register as zone disruption as much as it seems to be train prevention.</span></td>
