<br />

<br />
The only problem I see with AE kiting is the sheer amount of exp raked in from a 10 minute kite, especially at lower levels.  I still die several unrezzed deaths a night when AEing.  Heck, in the past 2 days, I've dinged 60 at least 4 times <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /> The exp hit for a death is just now in the high 50s and 60 starting to actually mean something.  A death now takes roughly 3/4 of my next kite to get back (I know, I know, I should kite more than the 20 or so mobs I grab at a time).  I remember at the cougars in Iceclad, I could round up all the cougars on one island and kite them down, run to the other island, kite them, and have most of a level.  A death there was meaningless as I would only lose about 2.5-3 blue each time.  With a souldbinder in the zone, it would take like 2 minutes to collect the body and start over.  It seems to me the risk V. reward has started to even out more the higher level I get.
<br />

<br />
On a side note, when I AE in Nadox, I usually grab all the troll mobs around the lava bridge.  This includes the entrance of the tunnels and the room that has 10 or so in it.  I've seen people say they can do the luggalds and undead as well.  Where do you start that pull from?  Undeads and luggald, then run back to bridge area and finish pull?
<br />

<br />
Frahlik Freely
<br />
60th Virtuoso of Seekers of Balance
<br />
Firiona Vie</span></td>
