				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: ae kiting<a name="36097"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 23 04 8:40 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Exp in Nadox isn't bad, at least not at 60.  I generally take it easy though... only around 25-30 mobs a pull.  I haven't had a problem with warping, but the mobs in Nadox do have a bug (probably intentional) to run an arc for only  a limited amount of time before taking a short break to go straight.  Easy to see, hard to explain.  This happens on all my kites in Nadox when the mobs get to ~50% life and isn't too bad to adjust for when it starts.  It also happens no matter how many people are in zone.  This might be the warping you are talking about.
<br />

<br />
Since I'm just 60, I can't compare the exp to BoT.  Also, apparently most people head to Nadox to kite the luggalds and undead.  I've been sticking to the trolls around the lava bridge and in the tunnels by it.  I die most when pulling, which is why I usually take the area in 2 pulls instead of 1 gigantic one of 60-80 mobs.  The slower exp/hour is more than made up for in the couple kpp i can make during that time.  
<br />

<br />
The most annoying thing I've found about this zone so far is the terrible pathing through some of the corridors.  The worst one is the doorway between the lava bridge room and the flat open room with ~15 trolls in it.  Mobs will just run back and forth at that entrance for minutes sometimes.  Since I pull all the mobs out of the flat room and do the kite in the open area of the lava bridge, I'll have stragglers who got caught in the doorway (running willy-nilly, not stuck on geometry) come running out that room while I'm rounding others up.  If I don't see them coming I tend to get stunned and take an early dirt nap <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Frahlik Freely
<br />
60th Virtuoso of Seekers of Balance
